title: Pictured Rocks National Lakeshore: Photo Gallery
body: Photo Gallery         Lars Jensen photo  Winter Photos Lars Jensen is a frequent winter visitor to the lakeshore with a knack for taking great photos such as this album from 2011.  http://www-personal.umich.edu/~jensenl/visuals/album/2011/chapel/                           The Pictured Rocks   15 Photos  While Pictured Rocks National Lakeshore is a mosaic of scenery, it is best known for its namesake sandstone cliffs that rise from Lake Superior.          Fall Colors   3 Photos  Pictured Rocks National Lakeshore is more than just the rocks. The maples, birches, pines, and other foliage combine for a beautiful mosaic of autumn color.          Beaches of Pictured Rocks   10 Photos  Lake Superior boasts beautiful beaches including those at Pictured Rocks National Lakeshore. Inland lakes are also fine places to find beaches.            Grand Sable Dunes and Banks   7 Photos  The five square mile Grand Sable Dunes are perched high atop the Grand Sable Banks on the shores of Lake Superior.          Waterfalls   7 Photos  Most of the waterfalls in this area are the result of water running over a shelf or cliffs of limey sandstone called the Munising Formation.
